  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd  \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u2013\u0b8f\u0b8e\u0bb5\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka is immobilized as fuel stocks run out - AVB",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "He mentioned that the situation will worsen tomorrow (Monday) as there is no way to get diesel.",
        "He said that bus services will be reduced on Monday and there is no possibility of an immediate solution.",
        "Sri Lanka has less than a day's supply of fuel, Energy Minister Kanchanavijaisekara said on Sunday, while public transport has been disrupted as the country's economic crisis deepens.",
        "Fuel queues stretch for several kilometers in the capital despite many petrol stations running out of fuel for days.",
        "Minister Kanjana Vijayasekara said that the country's petrol reserves are 4000 tonnes and this is not enough for one day's consumption.",
        "He told reporters that the next petrol ship will reach the country on the 22nd or 23rd.",
        "The Minister said that we have contacted other distributors but we cannot confirm that we will get new supply from 22nd.",
        "Last week, cash-strapped Sri Lanka announced a two-week emergency fuel supply to save petrol and diesel for emergency needs.",
        "Many shops remained closed on Sunday and the situation is expected to worsen when banks and trading posts reopen on Monday.",
        "It was seen that the trapped people were trying to escape from the few vehicles found on the streets.",
        "Private buses, which account for two-thirds of the country's bus service, were hit hard by fuel shortages, with very limited plying on Sunday.",
        "Kemunuwijayaratna, President of the Private Bus Owners Association, said that out of 20,000 buses owned by our association members, only 1,000 buses were put into service.",
        "He mentioned that the situation will worsen tomorrow (Monday) as there is no way to get diesel.",
        "He said that bus services will be reduced on Monday and there is no possibility of an immediate solution.",
        "Tricycles, Sri Lanka's popular form of transport, were also absent from the streets, with many tricycles queuing up to get six liters of petrol on a rationing basis."
      ],
